ild.gradle if needed.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering dependencies in Gradle**\\n\\nI think I need to exclude the missing main jar as well. It seems that replacing a dependency is different from adding another one. Right now, using `testImplementation \\\"net.minidev:accessors-smart:$libraryVersion\\\"` is causing a missing issue. Maybe I should replace that with the sources classifier and ASM. It’s a bit tricky, but getting the dependencies right is essential for everything to compile and run smoothly!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_EnXrtwbMWgRFRYqHJ2RvWB6m|fc_0bf37a218e1fdef5016a24498985808195bac2a7222a576e52", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/net.minidev/accessors-smart/2.4.3/build.gradle", "edits": [{"oldText": "dependencies {\n    testImplementation \"net.minidev:accessors-smart:$libraryVersion\"\n    testImplementation 'org.assertj:assertj-core:3.22.0'\n}\n", "newText": "dependencies {\n    testImplementation \"net.minidev:accessors-smart:$libraryVersion:sources\"\n    testImplementation 'org.ow2.asm:asm:8.0.1'\n    testImplementation 'org.assertj:assertj-core:3.22.0'\n}\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 578, "output": 1183, "cacheRead": 22016, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 23777, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780762991175, "responseId": "resp_0bf37a218e1fdef5016a24496fddd48195972acca89564264b"}}
